                    "id": "B.I.1",
                    "title": "Executive summary",
                    "heading_level": 3,
                    "blocks": [
                        {
                            "type": "callout",
                            "iaja": "J",
                            "text": "ESA confirms Triaging thesis with higher conviction. Evo traction in Europe (~50% of orders) validates product differentiation. Margin recovery to 40.3% gross margin in Q4 confirms restructuring execution. Unity MR-Linac sole provider position post-ViewRay bankruptcy is underappreciated optionality. IC strengthens from C to C+. Starter position justified at ~SEK 62.",
                            "kind": "verdict"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "prose",
                            "iaja": "A",
                            "text": "ESA-depth analysis adds three layers beyond Triaging: (1) Q4 gross margin hit 40.3%, confirming restructuring savings are flowing through faster than expected — SEK 500M annualised savings on track. (2) Evo European order data (~50% of volume) validates that 30% price premium is not eroding under competitive pressure — hospitals are paying for AI-enhanced adaptive therapy. (3) Unity sole provider position post-ViewRay creates underappreciated optionality — if adaptive RT adoption inflects, Elekta is the only supplier. Risk assessment: Varian TrueBeam replacement (autumn 2026) is the binding competitive constraint; China share erosion from United Imaging is the structural risk."
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "bullet_group",
                            "items": [
                                {
                                    "iaja": "J",
                                    "text": "PRIMARY driver: Margin recovery via restructuring + Evo pricing — SEK 500M savings + 30% price premium on Evo = EBIT path from 11.9% to 14%+.",
                                    "sub": [
                                        {
                                            "iaja": "I",
                                            "text": "Q4 FY25/26: GM 40.3% confirms trajectory. EBIT improving. Full SEK 500M savings on track for FY26/27."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "iaja": "A",
                                            "text": "Target: 14%+ EBIT margin, 40%+ gross margin. Evo pricing + COGS reduction + SaaS mix shift are three margin levers."
                                        }
                                    ]
                                },
                                {
                                    "iaja": "J",
                                    "text": "SECONDARY driver: US market penetration — 66% of US linacs >8 years old, Evo FDA clearance triggers replacement cycle, double-digit US order growth emerging.",
                                    "sub": [
                                        {
                                            "iaja": "I",
                                            "text": "Elekta US share <15% (down from >20%). Evo FDA cleared Jan 2026. US linac fleet is oldest in decades."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "iaja": "A",
                                            "text": "US order growth is the key confirmation signal. Q4 FY25/26 US data (May 2026) will be fulcrum."
                                        }
                                    ]
                                },
                                {
                                    "iaja": "J",
                                    "text": "TERTIARY driver: China recovery + software SaaS transition — book-to-bill >1.1, SaaS at 80% more revenue per customer vs perpetual licence.",
                                    "sub": [
                                        {
                                            "iaja": "I",
                                            "text": "China 40-45% share but under pressure from United Imaging (+17.7pp H1 2025). SaaS 25% of new software orders."
                                        },
                                        {
                                            "iaja": "A",
                                            "text": "China share stabilisation >40% is hygiene assumption. SaaS transition compounds over time but is not near-term catalyst."
                                        }
                                    ]
                                }
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "prose",
                            "iaja": "A",
                            "text": "Key risk assessment updated: (i) Varian TrueBeam platform — competitive specs unknown until autumn 2026; probability of feature-match at launch estimated 40-50%. If matched, Evo premium erodes from 30% to 15-20%. Impact: 150-200bps gross margin reduction. Manageable but dampens upside. (ii) United Imaging China — share loss rate decelerating per Q3 commentary. If China stabilises >40% share, this risk becomes YELLOW not ORANGE. (iii) FX — structural headwind but manageable given SEK weakness trend. Net risk assessment: YELLOW (from ORANGE at Triaging)."
                        }
                    ],
